NPDS_Mongo contains database related code for "Using MongoDB and Mongoose with a MEAN Stack Implementation of the NEXUS-PORTAL-DOORS System"

In order to run any of the files, start up a MongoDB instance: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/mongo/
Then, open a Node.js console and traverse to the directory where NPDS_Mongo is stored.

To run the file, simply type node <filename>

insert.js: creates and inserts resources into a NPDS database with Nexus, Portal, and Doors collections. The varaibles at the top of the file (name, nature, type, and author) will evnetually be fed info from client side or webcrawler.

search.js: looks for resources created by a certain author 

retrieveResource.js: looks for resource based on handle/tag
